A4.text: Ohio State has won a championship in the Big Ten 39 times, second‑most in the conference.

A5.text: Ohio State vacated 12 wins and its Big Ten title in 2010 due to NCAA sanctions.

A6.text: During the 2005–2006 school year, Ohio State became the first Big Ten team to win conference championships in football, men's basketball and women's basketball.

A7.text: Penn State has four Big Ten Conference championships in 1994, 2005, 2008 and 2016.
